 Browne'', [[Kenelm Digby]]'s ''Observations on Religio Medici'', and [[Alexander Ross (writer)|Alexander Ross]]'s ''Medicus Medicatus''; and background material, such as many of Browne's sources.\n* [http://essays.quotidiana.org/browne/ Quotations by Sir Thomas Browne] at [http://essays.quotidiana.org/ Quotidiana.org].\n* [http://www.bbk.ac.uk/english/tbs/default.htm The Thomas Browne Seminar]\n*  Various essays on Browne at [http://aquariumofvulcan.blogspot.com/ Aquarium of Vulcan]\n* [http://levity.com/alchemy/sir_thomas_browne.html Alchemical and Hermetic thought in the literary works of Sir Thomas Browne]\n* [http://www.umilta.net/browne.html Spiritual and literary affinity between Julian of Norwich and Sir Thomas Browne].\n* [http://www.umilta.net/thosbrowne.html Prayer and Prophecy in Browne's life and writings].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110814063251/http://www3.wooster.edu/artfuldodge/interviews/borges.htm Interview with Jorge Luis Borges, 25 April 1980, discussing Browne]\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Browne,+Thomas,+Sir | name=Thomas Browne}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Sir Thomas Browne}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=2989}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070715000218/http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/?pa=quote&sa=browseQuotesFrontEnd&pageNum=2&resultsPerPage=20&sortLetter=b Sir Thomas Browne Quotes] at [https://web.archive.org/web/20070713083148/http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/ Convergence]\n* [https://www.jstor.org/stable/29507065?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents \"Sir Thomas Browne: The Man And The Physician\"] by A. Batty Shaw, ''[[British Medical Journal]]'' (Clinical Research Edition), Vol. 285, No. 6334 (Jul. 3, 1982), pp.&nbsp;40\u201342\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Browne, Thomas}}\n[[Category:English science writers]]\n[[Category:English non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:English encyclopedists]]\n[[Category:Protestant mystics]]\n[[Category:Christian Kabbalists]]\n[[Category:Physiognomists]]\n[[Category:Paracelsians]]\n[