nd (Keith Eden)  which was intended for another woman.\n\nAustralian TV drama was relatively rare at the time.<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Stephen|last=Vagg|url=https://www.filmink.com.au/60-australian-tv-plays-1950s-60s/|magazine=Filmink|title=60 Australian TV Plays of the 1950s & \u201860s|date=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n==Cast==\n*[[Elspeth Ballantyne]]\n*Keith Eden\n*Betty Berrell\n*Tom Letch\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4077006}}\n\n{{Patrick Barton}}\n\n[[Category:Australian films]]\n[[Category:Australian television films]]\n[[Category:1963 television plays]]\n[[Category:Australian drama films]]\n\n\n{{Australia-tv-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Double Yolk\n| image          = \n| image size     =\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Patrick Barton]]\n| producer       =\n| writer         = [[Hugh Williams]]<br>[[Margaret Vyner|Margaret Williams]]\n| based on = \n| narrator       =\n| starring       = \n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio = ABC\n| distributor    = \n| released       = 26 June 1963<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article131724956 |title=THIS WEEK ON ABC3 |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |volume=37 |issue=10,570 |location=Australian Capital Territory, Australia |date=24 June 1963 |accessdate=19 February 2017 |page=16 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n| runtime        = 60 mins \n| country        = Australia\n| language       = [[English language|English]]\n| budget         = \n| gross = \n| preceded by    =\n| followed by    =\n}}\n'''''Double Yolk''''' is a 1963 Australian television play. It adapts two short plays, \"By Accident\" and \"With Intent\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article131724952 |title=No title |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |volume=37 |issue=10,570 |location=Australian Capital Territory, Australia |date=24 June 1963 |accessdate=19 Fe